<p itemprop="description">Security strategy involves developing and implementing comprehensive long-term plans for protecting government organizations from security threats while enabling digital transformation and service delivery.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand the importance of security strategy and recognise how security planning supports government objectives and digital transformation.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can contribute to security strategy development, understand security requirements, and align security activities with organizational goals.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can develop comprehensive security strategies, create security roadmaps, and establish frameworks for security governance and risk management.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can lead enterprise security strategy across government, influence security policy, and drive organizational transformation through strategic security initiatives.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

